	<entry>
		<title>First Aid Policy including Administration of Medicines</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="/index.php/early-years/early-years-policies/318-first-aid-policy-including-administration-of-medicines.html"/>
		<published>2015-01-31T15:43:33Z</published>
		<updated>2015-01-31T15:43:33Z</updated>
		<id>https://westwardschool.co.uk/index.php/early-years/early-years-policies/318-first-aid-policy-including-administration-of-medicines.html</id>
		<author>
			<name>Mrs Stevenson</name>
		<email>westwardschool@btconnect.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;First Aid Policy including Administration of Medicines&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;This policy applies to the Early Years/Out of School Care Facilities and the Main School.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;First Aid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Assessment of Need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The level of first aid provision (staff training, first aid kits and internal procedures) has been determined by risk assessment and shall be reviewed annually by the School Manager, or following a related incident, or feedback from interested parties, or significant changes to the school&amp;lsquo;s premises / activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;First&amp;nbsp;Aiders&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The School Manager (Mrs James) is the designated staff member responsible for administering first aid. They hold a current 3 year&amp;nbsp;paediatrics&amp;nbsp;12 hour first aid and anaphylaxis training certificate and shall keep their certification up-to-date through regular refresher training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	There will always be a member of staff on site who holds a full paediatrics first aid certificate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	There will also be a member of staff who holds a full 12 hour paediatrics first aid certificate for off site education i.e. school trips, School Journeys and sports activities such as Xcel Leisure Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Administrative Assistant (Miss K Ford) shall cover for the School Manager in their absence. They also hold a current 3 year 12 hour&amp;nbsp;paediatrics&amp;nbsp;first aid and anaphylaxis training certificate and shall keep their certification up-to-date through regular refresher training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Other staff members who hold a full 3 year&amp;nbsp;paediatrics&amp;nbsp;first aid and anaphylaxis training certificate and shall keep their certification up-to-date through regular refresher training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Mrs S Stevenson (Headteacher)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Mrs K Callaby (Early Years and Head of Lower School)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Mrs D Lawrence (Nursery)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12.16px; line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Mrs L Hannon (Early Years and Out of School Care Supervisor)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Miss H&amp;nbsp;Luksch (Year 1 and Upper School Sports)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All other staff members undertake the Level 2 Award &amp;#39;Emergency First Aid at Work&amp;#39; every 3 years. Last training carried out on 29/6/16.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Designated Sick Room&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	As required by the Education (School Premises) Regulations (1996), the room designated for care of pupils during school hours is in the old building on the lower ground floor. This room contains a first aid kit/running hot and cold water, wash facilities, privacy curtain and is adjacent to toilet and wash facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;First Aid Kits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	First aid kits are located in the following areas of the school:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Kitchen (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; School hall &amp;nbsp;(PLAYGROUND USE)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; All classrooms &amp;nbsp;(PLASTERS, ANTISEPTIC WIPES ETC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; School Manager&amp;rsquo;s office (off site first aid kits and kit items for replenishment use&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Staff room (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Sick room (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Early Years Section (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Outside Early Years Area (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All first aid kits are clearly identifiable and available to all staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	First aid kits are replenished regularly. Supplies are kept in the School Manager&amp;rsquo;s office. The School Manager is responsible for ensuring the contents of first aid kits are regularly checked, items are sterile/suitable for use, in-date, replenished when needed and stock ordered.&lt;br clear=&quot;all&quot; /&gt;
	First aid kits contain equipment relevant to their location, e.g. full kit in the kitchen, classroom kit in classrooms, playground kit in playgrounds,&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;bumbag&amp;nbsp;kit&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;coach kit&amp;rdquo; for off site activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In addition, the school has available &amp;quot;emergency&amp;quot; ventolin and salbutamol inhalers to be used in the event of a pupil or adult requiring aid in the absence of their personal inhaler. A list is also available informing the member of staff in charge as to which &amp;quot;perscription&amp;quot; inhaler the individual has been prescribed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Each full first aid kit contains the following in sealed packages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Waterproof plasters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Blue plasters (for kitchen staff).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Eye pad with bandage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Triangular bandages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Safety pins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Sterile dressings (assorted sizes).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Moist wipes. (medicated, alcohol free)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Disposable gloves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Medical Attention Procedure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Should a pupil suffer an accident or require urgent medical attention, the following procedure must be followed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Check for any immediate danger to the pupil.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Assess the pupil&amp;rsquo;s condition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If you are not a trained first&amp;nbsp;aider, request help from the nearest trained staff member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If necessary, call 999 - ask for an ambulance and answer all questions calmly (see contacting emergency services notice by all telephones).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Administer first aid as appropriate until help arrives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Arrange for a member of staff to contact the pupil&amp;rsquo;s parents/carer&amp;nbsp;and make them aware of the situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If parents/carer&amp;nbsp;cannot be contacted, leave a message asking them to contact the school urgently. The child&amp;#39;s emergency contact person may have to be informed in the case of parents being unavailable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The School Manager or another staff member must accompany the pupil to hospital and stay with them until their parent/carer&amp;nbsp;arrives. The pupil&amp;rsquo;s home message book or information card is to be taken with them to provide details of their emergency contact numbers, medical conditions, allergies and family doctor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Complete a Medical Incident Form and hand to the School Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Infectious Diseases&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The following arrangements are in place in order to&amp;nbsp;minimise&amp;nbsp;the risk to staff and pupils of infectious diseases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The School Manager is responsible for keeping abreast of any new information relating to infectious, notifiable and communicable diseases and local health issues. New information shall be disseminated to staff members and parents/carers&amp;nbsp;as necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Infectious diseases posters are displayed in the school office and staff room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If a pupil feels unwell, is sick, has&amp;nbsp;diarrhoea, has an accident and/or staff feel that they may have an infectious disease that may put other pupils/staff at risk, they will be isolated in the sick room and arrangements made for collection by their parent/carer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Emergency contact numbers will be used if the parent/carer&amp;nbsp;cannot be contacted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The pupil and parent&amp;rsquo;s right to confidentiality shall be respected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The pupil shall be treated in a sympathetic, caring and understanding manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Parents/carers&amp;nbsp;shall be kept informed of any infectious diseases occurring at the school.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We expect, and inform, parents/carers&amp;nbsp;to notify us if their child is suffering from any infectious disease that may put others at risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We expect, and inform, parents/carers to call or email the school office in the morning if their child is unwell and will not be attending school.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We expect, and inform, parents/carers to state the reasons for absence in their child&amp;rsquo;s home message book or email to the school office upon returning following illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Pupil Health Care Plans&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Westward School recognises that some pupils may have medical conditions that require support so that they can attend school regularly and take part in school activities. (Refer to Medical Conditions Policy)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Health Care Plans will be developed for all pupils with medical conditions requiring support during school time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Plans are developed with input from the parent/carer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Plans are reviewed as necessary by the Headteacher or School Manager or class teacher with input from the parent/carer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Parents/carers are expected to inform the school of any change in their child&amp;rsquo;s condition or medication requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Parents/carers are expected to supply the school with any life-saving prescription medication their child may require.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Relevant staff are briefed on the pupil&amp;rsquo;s medical requirements and administration of any medication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Medication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Competent staff members shall only administer prescription or non-prescription medication to pupils where there is a health reason to do so and we have received written consent from the parent/carer (e.g. penicillin, ear/eye drops, cough mixture, allergy creams &amp;amp; pills and travel sickness pills -&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;No Aspirin shall be administered&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; Staff members will not administer a greater dose than the official recommended dosage unless with doctor&amp;rsquo;s prescribed permission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Competent staff members shall only administer life-saving prescription medication to pupils in accordance with their health care plan and with written consent from their parent/carer (e.g. for anaphylaxis, asthma, diabetes, epilepsy).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Medicine consent forms for parental completion are located in the School Office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Westward School&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;47, Hersham Road, Walton on Thames, Surrey&amp;nbsp; KT12 1LE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Dear Parent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Please complete the following declaration for our First Aid records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	I authorise a member of staff at Westward School to administer the prescribed medication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;width:619px;&quot; width=&quot;619&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:54px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Date&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:122px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Child&amp;rsquo;s Name&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:123px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Time/s to administer the medication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:113px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Name of medication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:76px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Dosage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:130px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Time last dose administered&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:54px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:122px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:123px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:113px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:76px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:130px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Parent&amp;rsquo;s signature&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Date&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Records shall be kept by the School Manager of all medication administered to pupils.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All medication shall be stored in accordance with product instructions, in their original container and in a safe and secure location, out of reach of pupils.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Epipens&amp;nbsp;and inhalers are kept in a clearly marked bag, situated in the school office during class hours and on the playground hook during break times for quick access and under staff charge when child off site.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Anaphylaxis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	A list of pupils who may require the use of inhalers and epipens due to susceptibility to anaphylaxis is displayed in the staff room, Early Years rooms, lunch hall and school office, and kept up-to-date by the School Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All staff members have been trained in anaphylaxis awareness and the use of epipens and inhalers by a specialist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The following procedure regarding anaphylaxis is briefed to all staff members and regularly reviewed during staff meetings:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Educate susceptible pupils so that during playtimes they know what not to eat or touch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The pupil may be unwell if they exhibit the following symptoms:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Strange scratching at neck.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Strange unformed sentences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Wheezing / gasping for breath.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Tongue may be &amp;ldquo;tingling&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; This indicates their airway may be affected and requires action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Send for additional help and call an ambulance, stating anaphylaxis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Hold the pupil on your lap.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Administer adrenaline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Call their parent/carer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Administer a 2&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;dose if needed after 5 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Diabetes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The individual care plan will be followed, keeping parent/s informed at all times. All medical items i.e insulin, blood sugar level monitor, sweets/snacks kept in a single bag located in the school office during school hours. If the child is offsite this bag MUST ALWAYS BE WITH THE CHILD, UNDER A MEMBER OF STAFF&amp;#39;S SUPERVISION.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All contact details and care plan instructions in bag and posted in the staffroom in case of emergency. i.e. hypo situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	See&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://westwardschool.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&amp;amp;view=article&amp;amp;id=360&amp;amp;Itemid=108&quot;&gt;Medical Conditions Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong style=&quot;font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Accidents&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Accident Reporting - Internal&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All accidents, incidents, dangerous occurrences and near-misses, no matter how seemingly minor, must be reported to the School Manager without delay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	A Pupil Accident Book and a Staff Accident Book is located in the school office and must be completed following any accident. Details recorded include a brief description of the accident, who was involved, location, date, time and action taken.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The School Manager shall investigate all accidents, report their findings to the Headteacher and act accordingly to minimise the risk of further occurrences. Where equipment or systems of work are found to be a causal affect, remedial actions shall be taken immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Accident Book shall be reviewed annually by the School Manager and any trends identified reported to the Headteacher for action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Completed Accident Books must be kept for a minimum of 3 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Accident Reporting - HSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In accordance with the Reporting of Injuries, Diseases and Dangerous Occurrences Regulations (1995) (RIDDOR), the following must be reported to the HSE in writing by the School Manager within 10 days of occurring:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Deaths (to be reported by telephone without delay).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Major injuries (see HSE website for definitions - to be reported by telephone without delay).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Injuries to an employee resulting in them being unable to work for 3 or more consecutive days (including weekends).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Injuries to pupils, and other non-employees, through activities connected to the school&amp;rsquo;s activities, that lead to a hospital visit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Specified occupational diseases (see HSE website for guidance - to be reported by telephone without delay).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Specified dangerous occurrences (see HSE website for guidance - to be reported by telephone without delay).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Accidents - Pupils&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In addition, the following arrangements are in place should a pupil suffer an accident:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For EYFS and Out of School Care pupils, parents/carers are asked to sign the accident book entry, and informed by the home message book if not collecting their child.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For main school pupils, parents/carers are informed through the dismissal process, by telephone, email or the home message book (as applicable).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For Breakfast Club pupils, the staff member on duty must inform the class teacher about the accident when handover occurs so that the parent/carer can be informed at the end of the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Pupils suffering a minor head injury will be issued with an &amp;ldquo;I banged my head&amp;rdquo; slip and sticker. Parents will be notified in the event of a major head injury requiring hospital attention or &amp;ldquo;one to one&amp;rdquo; observation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px; line-height: 18.2399997711182px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Staff members will always wear gloves when dealing with the spillage of bodily fluids.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Last Reviewed: October 2016&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;First Aid Policy including Administration of Medicines&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;This policy applies to the Early Years/Out of School Care Facilities and the Main School.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;First Aid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Assessment of Need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The level of first aid provision (staff training, first aid kits and internal procedures) has been determined by risk assessment and shall be reviewed annually by the School Manager, or following a related incident, or feedback from interested parties, or significant changes to the school&amp;lsquo;s premises / activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;First&amp;nbsp;Aiders&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The School Manager (Mrs James) is the designated staff member responsible for administering first aid. They hold a current 3 year&amp;nbsp;paediatrics&amp;nbsp;12 hour first aid and anaphylaxis training certificate and shall keep their certification up-to-date through regular refresher training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	There will always be a member of staff on site who holds a full paediatrics first aid certificate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	There will also be a member of staff who holds a full 12 hour paediatrics first aid certificate for off site education i.e. school trips, School Journeys and sports activities such as Xcel Leisure Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Administrative Assistant (Miss K Ford) shall cover for the School Manager in their absence. They also hold a current 3 year 12 hour&amp;nbsp;paediatrics&amp;nbsp;first aid and anaphylaxis training certificate and shall keep their certification up-to-date through regular refresher training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Other staff members who hold a full 3 year&amp;nbsp;paediatrics&amp;nbsp;first aid and anaphylaxis training certificate and shall keep their certification up-to-date through regular refresher training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Mrs S Stevenson (Headteacher)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Mrs K Callaby (Early Years and Head of Lower School)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Mrs D Lawrence (Nursery)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12.16px; line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;Mrs L Hannon (Early Years and Out of School Care Supervisor)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Miss H&amp;nbsp;Luksch (Year 1 and Upper School Sports)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All other staff members undertake the Level 2 Award &amp;#39;Emergency First Aid at Work&amp;#39; every 3 years. Last training carried out on 29/6/16.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Designated Sick Room&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	As required by the Education (School Premises) Regulations (1996), the room designated for care of pupils during school hours is in the old building on the lower ground floor. This room contains a first aid kit/running hot and cold water, wash facilities, privacy curtain and is adjacent to toilet and wash facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;First Aid Kits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	First aid kits are located in the following areas of the school:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Kitchen (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; School hall &amp;nbsp;(PLAYGROUND USE)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; All classrooms &amp;nbsp;(PLASTERS, ANTISEPTIC WIPES ETC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; School Manager&amp;rsquo;s office (off site first aid kits and kit items for replenishment use&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Staff room (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Sick room (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Early Years Section (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Outside Early Years Area (FULL KIT)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All first aid kits are clearly identifiable and available to all staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	First aid kits are replenished regularly. Supplies are kept in the School Manager&amp;rsquo;s office. The School Manager is responsible for ensuring the contents of first aid kits are regularly checked, items are sterile/suitable for use, in-date, replenished when needed and stock ordered.&lt;br clear=&quot;all&quot; /&gt;
	First aid kits contain equipment relevant to their location, e.g. full kit in the kitchen, classroom kit in classrooms, playground kit in playgrounds,&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;bumbag&amp;nbsp;kit&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;coach kit&amp;rdquo; for off site activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In addition, the school has available &amp;quot;emergency&amp;quot; ventolin and salbutamol inhalers to be used in the event of a pupil or adult requiring aid in the absence of their personal inhaler. A list is also available informing the member of staff in charge as to which &amp;quot;perscription&amp;quot; inhaler the individual has been prescribed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Each full first aid kit contains the following in sealed packages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Waterproof plasters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Blue plasters (for kitchen staff).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Eye pad with bandage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Triangular bandages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Safety pins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Sterile dressings (assorted sizes).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Moist wipes. (medicated, alcohol free)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Disposable gloves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Medical Attention Procedure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Should a pupil suffer an accident or require urgent medical attention, the following procedure must be followed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Check for any immediate danger to the pupil.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Assess the pupil&amp;rsquo;s condition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If you are not a trained first&amp;nbsp;aider, request help from the nearest trained staff member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If necessary, call 999 - ask for an ambulance and answer all questions calmly (see contacting emergency services notice by all telephones).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Administer first aid as appropriate until help arrives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Arrange for a member of staff to contact the pupil&amp;rsquo;s parents/carer&amp;nbsp;and make them aware of the situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If parents/carer&amp;nbsp;cannot be contacted, leave a message asking them to contact the school urgently. The child&amp;#39;s emergency contact person may have to be informed in the case of parents being unavailable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The School Manager or another staff member must accompany the pupil to hospital and stay with them until their parent/carer&amp;nbsp;arrives. The pupil&amp;rsquo;s home message book or information card is to be taken with them to provide details of their emergency contact numbers, medical conditions, allergies and family doctor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Complete a Medical Incident Form and hand to the School Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Infectious Diseases&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The following arrangements are in place in order to&amp;nbsp;minimise&amp;nbsp;the risk to staff and pupils of infectious diseases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The School Manager is responsible for keeping abreast of any new information relating to infectious, notifiable and communicable diseases and local health issues. New information shall be disseminated to staff members and parents/carers&amp;nbsp;as necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Infectious diseases posters are displayed in the school office and staff room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If a pupil feels unwell, is sick, has&amp;nbsp;diarrhoea, has an accident and/or staff feel that they may have an infectious disease that may put other pupils/staff at risk, they will be isolated in the sick room and arrangements made for collection by their parent/carer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Emergency contact numbers will be used if the parent/carer&amp;nbsp;cannot be contacted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The pupil and parent&amp;rsquo;s right to confidentiality shall be respected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The pupil shall be treated in a sympathetic, caring and understanding manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Parents/carers&amp;nbsp;shall be kept informed of any infectious diseases occurring at the school.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We expect, and inform, parents/carers&amp;nbsp;to notify us if their child is suffering from any infectious disease that may put others at risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We expect, and inform, parents/carers to call or email the school office in the morning if their child is unwell and will not be attending school.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We expect, and inform, parents/carers to state the reasons for absence in their child&amp;rsquo;s home message book or email to the school office upon returning following illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Pupil Health Care Plans&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Westward School recognises that some pupils may have medical conditions that require support so that they can attend school regularly and take part in school activities. (Refer to Medical Conditions Policy)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Health Care Plans will be developed for all pupils with medical conditions requiring support during school time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Plans are developed with input from the parent/carer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Plans are reviewed as necessary by the Headteacher or School Manager or class teacher with input from the parent/carer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Parents/carers are expected to inform the school of any change in their child&amp;rsquo;s condition or medication requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Parents/carers are expected to supply the school with any life-saving prescription medication their child may require.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Relevant staff are briefed on the pupil&amp;rsquo;s medical requirements and administration of any medication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Medication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Competent staff members shall only administer prescription or non-prescription medication to pupils where there is a health reason to do so and we have received written consent from the parent/carer (e.g. penicillin, ear/eye drops, cough mixture, allergy creams &amp;amp; pills and travel sickness pills -&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;No Aspirin shall be administered&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; Staff members will not administer a greater dose than the official recommended dosage unless with doctor&amp;rsquo;s prescribed permission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Competent staff members shall only administer life-saving prescription medication to pupils in accordance with their health care plan and with written consent from their parent/carer (e.g. for anaphylaxis, asthma, diabetes, epilepsy).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Medicine consent forms for parental completion are located in the School Office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Westward School&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;47, Hersham Road, Walton on Thames, Surrey&amp;nbsp; KT12 1LE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Dear Parent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Please complete the following declaration for our First Aid records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	I authorise a member of staff at Westward School to administer the prescribed medication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;width:619px;&quot; width=&quot;619&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:54px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Date&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:122px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Child&amp;rsquo;s Name&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:123px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Time/s to administer the medication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:113px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Name of medication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:76px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Dosage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:130px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Time last dose administered&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:54px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:122px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:123px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:113px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:76px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width:130px;height:52px;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Parent&amp;rsquo;s signature&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Date&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Records shall be kept by the School Manager of all medication administered to pupils.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All medication shall be stored in accordance with product instructions, in their original container and in a safe and secure location, out of reach of pupils.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Epipens&amp;nbsp;and inhalers are kept in a clearly marked bag, situated in the school office during class hours and on the playground hook during break times for quick access and under staff charge when child off site.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Anaphylaxis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	A list of pupils who may require the use of inhalers and epipens due to susceptibility to anaphylaxis is displayed in the staff room, Early Years rooms, lunch hall and school office, and kept up-to-date by the School Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All staff members have been trained in anaphylaxis awareness and the use of epipens and inhalers by a specialist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The following procedure regarding anaphylaxis is briefed to all staff members and regularly reviewed during staff meetings:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Educate susceptible pupils so that during playtimes they know what not to eat or touch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The pupil may be unwell if they exhibit the following symptoms:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Strange scratching at neck.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Strange unformed sentences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Wheezing / gasping for breath.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:24pt;&quot;&gt;
	o&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Tongue may be &amp;ldquo;tingling&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; This indicates their airway may be affected and requires action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Send for additional help and call an ambulance, stating anaphylaxis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Hold the pupil on your lap.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Administer adrenaline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Call their parent/carer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Administer a 2&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;dose if needed after 5 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Diabetes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The individual care plan will be followed, keeping parent/s informed at all times. All medical items i.e insulin, blood sugar level monitor, sweets/snacks kept in a single bag located in the school office during school hours. If the child is offsite this bag MUST ALWAYS BE WITH THE CHILD, UNDER A MEMBER OF STAFF&amp;#39;S SUPERVISION.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All contact details and care plan instructions in bag and posted in the staffroom in case of emergency. i.e. hypo situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	See&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://westwardschool.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&amp;amp;view=article&amp;amp;id=360&amp;amp;Itemid=108&quot;&gt;Medical Conditions Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong style=&quot;font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Accidents&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Accident Reporting - Internal&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All accidents, incidents, dangerous occurrences and near-misses, no matter how seemingly minor, must be reported to the School Manager without delay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	A Pupil Accident Book and a Staff Accident Book is located in the school office and must be completed following any accident. Details recorded include a brief description of the accident, who was involved, location, date, time and action taken.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The School Manager shall investigate all accidents, report their findings to the Headteacher and act accordingly to minimise the risk of further occurrences. Where equipment or systems of work are found to be a causal affect, remedial actions shall be taken immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Accident Book shall be reviewed annually by the School Manager and any trends identified reported to the Headteacher for action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Completed Accident Books must be kept for a minimum of 3 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Accident Reporting - HSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In accordance with the Reporting of Injuries, Diseases and Dangerous Occurrences Regulations (1995) (RIDDOR), the following must be reported to the HSE in writing by the School Manager within 10 days of occurring:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Deaths (to be reported by telephone without delay).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Major injuries (see HSE website for definitions - to be reported by telephone without delay).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Injuries to an employee resulting in them being unable to work for 3 or more consecutive days (including weekends).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Injuries to pupils, and other non-employees, through activities connected to the school&amp;rsquo;s activities, that lead to a hospital visit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Specified occupational diseases (see HSE website for guidance - to be reported by telephone without delay).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Specified dangerous occurrences (see HSE website for guidance - to be reported by telephone without delay).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Accidents - Pupils&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In addition, the following arrangements are in place should a pupil suffer an accident:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For EYFS and Out of School Care pupils, parents/carers are asked to sign the accident book entry, and informed by the home message book if not collecting their child.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For main school pupils, parents/carers are informed through the dismissal process, by telephone, email or the home message book (as applicable).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For Breakfast Club pupils, the staff member on duty must inform the class teacher about the accident when handover occurs so that the parent/carer can be informed at the end of the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Pupils suffering a minor head injury will be issued with an &amp;ldquo;I banged my head&amp;rdquo; slip and sticker. Parents will be notified in the event of a major head injury requiring hospital attention or &amp;ldquo;one to one&amp;rdquo; observation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:12pt;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px; line-height: 18.2399997711182px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Staff members will always wear gloves when dealing with the spillage of bodily fluids.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Last Reviewed: October 2016&lt;/p&gt;</content>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<title>Food and Drink Policy</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="/index.php/early-years/early-years-policies/51-food-and-drink-policy.html"/>
		<published>2010-08-29T15:12:10Z</published>
		<updated>2010-08-29T15:12:10Z</updated>
		<id>https://westwardschool.co.uk/index.php/early-years/early-years-policies/51-food-and-drink-policy.html</id>
		<author>
			<name>Mrs Stevenson</name>
		<email>westwardschool@btconnect.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
	&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;
		&lt;u&gt;Food and Drink and Healthy Eating Policy&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;AIM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	We &lt;span data-scayt_word=&quot;recognise&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;1&quot;&gt;recognise&lt;/span&gt; that snack and meal times are an important part of the child&amp;rsquo;s day. It is a social time for children to enjoy food. We aim to provide healthy, balanced, varied and nutritious food and drink to meet the child&amp;rsquo;s needs and encourage them to develop and promote healthy lifestyles and well-being throughout their life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;We meet the welfare requirements outlined in the &lt;span data-scayt_word=&quot;EYFS&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;2&quot;&gt;EYFS&lt;/span&gt; on food and drink: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left: 36pt&quot;&gt;
	&lt;em&gt;&amp;lsquo;Where children are provided with meals, snacks and drinks, they must be healthy, balanced and nutritious.&amp;rsquo; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;IMPLEMENTATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;h2&gt;
			&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: times new roman,times,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px&quot;&gt;Before a child starts here at Westward we find out from parents their child&amp;rsquo;s special&amp;nbsp;dietary&amp;nbsp;requirements, including any cultural, religious or medical reasons; preferences or food allergies. Parents complete&amp;nbsp;admission forms containing this information, and discuss with the practitioners / key person, children&amp;rsquo;s dietary needs. All practitioners have a file in their class containing this important information. This information is then shared with the relevant persons, including the school cook.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		We regularly consult with parents about children&amp;rsquo;s dietary requirements that have changed. The relevant forms are then updated.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		We display a chart with the child&amp;rsquo;s name and individual dietary needs in the staff room, each class has their own copy and in the school kitchen so all staff and volunteers know about them. In the Nursery and Reception rooms we have a dietary sheet and at lunch the school cook and supervisors are aware of those children who need to get food and drink consistent with their needs and / or parental wishes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;SNACK &amp;amp; MEAL TIMES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		The lunch menu is on a rolling three week rota which is based on and considers parental views. This menu is enclosed in the early years handbook; shared during the new parents meeting; and displayed on the early years notice board and around the school.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		The menu is &lt;span data-scayt_word=&quot;organised&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;3&quot;&gt;organised&lt;/span&gt; to provide a healthy, nutritious and balanced diet. High-quality produce is sought that avoid large quantities of fat, salt and sugar and artificial &lt;span data-scayt_word=&quot;colouring&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;4&quot;&gt;colouring&lt;/span&gt;, additives or preservatives. Fresh fruit and vegetables are provided daily. We provide a varied diet, in which we encourage children to try familiar and unfamiliar foods. We also encourage children to talk about and make healthy choices. Children with special requirements are catered for, such as vegetarian options are provided daily. Parents may wish to bring in food due to dietary requirements which they may do so in consultation with the staff, to ensure food is nutritious and well-balanced, which is then stored safely.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		For snack, we ask parents for a contribution of &amp;pound;1.50 per week which is used to buy fruit and vegetables for the children and a hot snack on a Thursday. We also use some of this money to buy ingredients for cookery sessions with the children.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Snack and meal times are treated as a social event to develop healthy practices whilst maintaining good food hygiene.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		We operate a snack bar in each of the early years rooms with the support of early years practitioners/parents. The children are encouraged to prepare the snack (with due care given to hygiene). Children choose their snack, including a drink of semi-skimmed milk or water which is available all morning until 11.00am.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		At lunch, Nursery and Reception children sit with an early years practitioner to encourage a positive eating experience. The children have a choice of food and drink and practitioners encourage children to make their own choices and talk to them about their decisions. At snack, children serve themselves. At lunch, the school cook serves the children after they have made their choice. They are all encouraged to eat their lunch with a knife and fork.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Children who come to before and/or after school care are provided with breakfast and tea, in accordance with parental wishes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Food hygiene is considered of the upmost importance. All practitioners who handle or serve food are trained in food hygiene during their induction and then regularly reviewed to enable them to handle food safely. We are registered with the Local Authority.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		All food is stored safely in accordance with environmental regulation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Children are informed to eat the foods on their plate. As a class prior to our first meal, we discuss sensitively that the foods on our plates may be different and that for us all to be safe we must not swap foods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Practitioners / key person / school manager is available at the end of the day / session if parents wish to talk about the menu or what the child has consumed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		We are aware that some children may not want to eat what is provided. However, we do find that when children are sitting with their friends, they like to eat what their classmates are eating. If children&amp;rsquo;s food intake/diet is cause for concern or limited, we speak to the parents to cater for the child&amp;rsquo;s preferences and gradually expose them to more foods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;DRINKING WATER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		We encourage and support children to drink throughout the day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Children (and staff) have access to drinking water at all times throughout the day. Children can independently serve themselves using the jug and disposable water cups available inside and water fountains outside/cups and jug. The jug is filled for the beginning of the session and re-filled as and when needed which is sterilized at the end of the day. Children also have a drink at snack and at lunch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;u&gt;Curriculum&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		As part of the curriculum we discuss healthy practices, including the need to drink water after physical exercise, hot weather.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		We also discuss healthy eating. We help children to understand why some foods are healthy and others are not.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Children participate in cooking activities and gardening. They try foods from a range of cultures (respecting parental views and taking into consideration children&amp;rsquo;s dietary requirements).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Policy Last Updated: November 2016&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
